cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a neural network-based liver segmentation algorithm using fully convolutional networks (FCN) and self-supervising schemes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep supervision and volumetric image segmentation further supports the possibility of the paper belonging to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of CT images also suggests that the paper may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the application of neural networks for segmentation indicates that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
